Allow us to re-introduce Ayo Van Elmar, an Afro-European fusion fashion brand – as she unveils her 2020 Spring/Summer Collection at the Ayo Van Elmar ‘Fashion Party”. The Fashion Party is set to hold on Saturday, 17th August 2019 at the Ayo Van Elmar Fashion Café, Oriental Hotel Victoria Island in partnership with Rent-a-party. It promises to be an evening of exquisite fashion and an ambience reminiscent of summer in Paris.
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-990858 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-AVE-shopping-party-598x598.jpeg" alt="" width="1280" height="1280" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-AVE-shopping-party-598x598.jpeg 598w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-AVE-shopping-party-100x100.jpeg 100w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-AVE-shopping-party-200x200.jpeg 200w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-AVE-shopping-party-487x487.jpeg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-AVE-shopping-party-974x974.jpeg 974w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-AVE-shopping-party-240x240.jpeg 240w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-AVE-shopping-party-480x480.jpeg 480w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-AVE-shopping-party-600x600.jpeg 600w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-AVE-shopping-party.jpeg 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> As a pre-event activity in readiness for the shopping party event and with Ayo Van Elmar penchant for giving back to society, she will be hosting a fashion Brunch tagged ‘So You Wanna Do Fashion’ where she will have other fashion and lifestyle creatives speak in clear terms, what it takes to navigate the hurdles in the Nigerian Fashion industry; its strengths and weaknesses, opportunities and obstacles. Ayo Van Elmar is a fast-emerging brand that was launched in May 2011 and has indeed grown by leaps and bounds. AVE’s style can be described as Afro-European fusion fashion that is inspired by the creative director’s multicultural experience. AVE Fashion Brunch Ayo Van Elmar has successfully showcased collections at the Nigeria, Vienna and London fashion week. Ayo Van Elmar was also contracted to design the wardrobe for the TV shows; Nigeria’s Got Talent (2012) and Glo X-Factor West Africa (2013)
Ayo Elizabeth Olaogun the brains behind the AVE pieces stated, “fashion is more than clothes, fashion is a statement, fashion is art, fashion is the impression you leave behind when you walk out of the room. The SS20 collection is called “Salt” because it a translation of a style that never loses its appeal”
Rent-a-party (RAP), Nigeria’s No. 1 online event rental company would be bringing the venue to life with exquisite décor and dashing lights.
Mark you calendars and save the date, this is one fashion party you don’t want to miss.